-- Phil Mickelson Has Three-Shot Lead in British Open Final Round
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-07-21T16:16:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-21/phil-mickelson-has-three-shot-lead-in-british-open-final-round.html
Phil Mickelson  has a three-stroke
lead in the final round of the British Open after shooting a 5-under par 66.  Mickelson birdied the 18th hole at Muirfield in Gullane,
Scotland, to finish with a score of 3-under 281. He’s trying to
win his first British Open title and the fifth major
championship of his career.  England’s Lee Westwood and Henrik Stenson of Sweden are
tied for second at even par. Westwood has played 15 holes today
and Stenson is through 17.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  